{
  "id": "celery_celery_10313",
  "repo_name": "celery/celery",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/celery/celery",
  "base_commit": "8dace6d94b7714db4c677ccea824bc5fee1fdede",
  "pr_number": 10313,
  "issue_number": 10312,
  "issue_title": "redis_backend_use_ssl raises ValueError with redis:// scheme, but broker_use_ssl works fine \u2014 inconsistent SSL handling between broker and backend",
  "issue_body": "# Checklist\n  - [x] I have verified that the issue exists against the `main` branch of Celery.\n  - [x] This has already been asked to the discussions forum first.\n  - [x] I have read the relevant section in the contribution guide on reporting bugs.\n  - [x] I have checked the issues list for similar or identical bug reports.\n  - [x] I have checked the pull requests list for existing proposed fixes.\n  - [x] I have checked the commit log to find out if the bug was already fixed in the main branch.\n  - [x] I have included all related issues and possible duplicate issues in this issue.\n  - [ ] I have tried to reproduce the issue with pytest-celery (not applicable \u2014 issue is in startup validation, not task execution)\n\n  ## Mandatory Debugging Information\n  - [x] I have included the output of `celery -A proj report` in the issue.\n  - [x] I have included the contents of `pip freeze` in the issue.\n  - [x] I have included all the versions of all the external dependencies required to reproduce this bug.\n\n  ## Optional Debugging Information\n  - [ ] I have tried reproducing the issue on more than one Python version\n  - [ ] I have tried reproducing the issue on more than one message broker and/or result backend\n\n  ## Related Issues and Possible Duplicates\n\n  #### Related Issues\n  - None found\n\n  #### Possible Duplicates\n  - None found\n\n  ## Environment & Settings\n\n  **Celery version**: 5.6.3\n\n  <details>\n  <summary><b><code>celery report</code> Output:</b></summary>\n  <p>\n\n  software -> celery:5.6.3 (recovery) kombu:5.6.2 py:3.12.13\n              billiard:4.2.4 redis-py:6.4.0\n  platform -> system:Linux arch:64bit imp:CPython\n  loader   -> celery.loaders.app.AppLoader\n  settings -> transport:redis results:rediss\n\n  </p>\n  </details>\n\n  # Steps to Reproduce\n\n  ## Required Dependencies\n  - **Minimal Python Version**: 3.12\n  - **Minimal Celery Version**: 5.6.3 (likely earlier versions too)\n  - **Minimal Kombu Version**: 5.6.2\n  - **Minimal Broker Version**: Redis 7.x (AWS ElastiCache, TLS-only)\n  - **Minimal Result Backend Version**: same Redis instance\n  - **Minimal OS and/or Kernel Version**: Linux (EKS / Amazon Linux)\n  - **Minimal Broker Client Version**: redis-py 6.4.0\n  - **Minimal Result Backend Client Version**: redis-py 6.4.0\n\n  ### Python Packages\n  <details>\n  <summary><b><code>pip freeze</code> Output:</b></summary>\n  <p>\n\n  amqp==5.3.1\n  billiard==4.2.4\n  celery==5.6.3\n  kombu==5.6.2\n  redis==6.4.0\n  vine==5.1.0\n\n  </p>\n  </details>\n\n  ### Other Dependencies\n  <details>\n  <p>\n  AWS ElastiCache Redis (TLS-only endpoint, no plain TCP connections accepted).\n  The broker and result backend point to the same Redis instance.\n  </p>\n  </details>\n\n  ## Minimally Reproducible Test Case\n\n  <details>\n  <p>\n\n  ```python\n  import ssl\n  from celery import Celery\n\n  # AWS ElastiCache or any TLS-only Redis endpoint\n  REDIS_URL = \"redis://:password@my-redis.cache.amazonaws.com:6379/0\"\n\n  ssl_options = {\"ssl_cert_reqs\": ssl.CERT_NONE}\n\n  # This raises ValueError on worker startup:\n  #   \"SSL connection parameters have been provided but the specified URL scheme\n  #    is redis://. A Redis SSL connection URL should use the scheme rediss://.\"\n  app = Celery(\n      \"myapp\",\n      broker=REDIS_URL,\n      backend=REDIS_URL,          # redis:// here causes the crash\n      broker_use_ssl=ssl_options,\n      redis_backend_use_ssl=ssl_options,\n  )\n\n  # Workaround: use different URL schemes for broker and backend\n  REDIS_URL_TLS = \"rediss://:password@my-redis.cache.amazonaws.com:6379/0\"\n\n  app = Celery(\n      \"myapp\",\n      broker=REDIS_URL,           # redis:// works with broker_use_ssl via Kombu\n      backend=REDIS_URL_TLS,      # rediss:// required by Celery backend\n      broker_use_ssl=ssl_options,\n      redis_backend_use_ssl=ssl_options,\n  )\n\n  Expected Behavior\n\n  Both broker_use_ssl and redis_backend_use_ssl should accept the same URL scheme, or the documentation should clearly state the asymmetry.\n\n  A user connecting to a TLS-only Redis naturally uses the same URL and SSL config for both broker and backend. The current behavior forces them to use redis:// for the broker and rediss:// for the backend \u2014\n  an inconsistency that is not documented and produces a cryptic CRITICAL/MainProcess Unrecoverable error on worker startup.\n\n  Alternatively, Kombu's broker transport should also raise (or at least warn) when broker_use_ssl is combined with a redis:// URL scheme, to match the backend's strict validation. Currently Kombu silently\n  accepts it (and it happens to work in 5.6.x), while the backend hard-rejects it.\n\n  Actual Behavior\n\n  Worker crashes immediately at startup with:\n\n  [CRITICAL/MainProcess] Unrecoverable error: ValueError(\n  '\\nSSL connection parameters have been provided but the specified URL\n  scheme is redis://. A Redis SSL connection URL should use the scheme rediss://.\\n')\n\n  Traceback (most recent call last):\n    File \"celery/worker/worker.py\", line 203, in start\n      self.blueprint.start(self)\n    File \"celery/apps/worker.py\", line 238, in startup_info\n      results=self.app.backend.as_uri(),\n    File \"celery/app/base.py\", line 1474, in backend\n      self._backend = self._get_backend()\n    File \"celery/backends/redis.py\", line 279, in __init__\n      self.connparams = self._params_from_url(url, self.connparams)\n    File \"celery/backends/redis.py\", line 343, in _params_from_url\n      raise ValueError(E_REDIS_SSL_PARAMS_AND_SCHEME_MISMATCH)\n  ValueError:\n  SSL connection parameters have been provided but the specified URL scheme\n  is redis://. A Redis SSL connection URL should use the scheme rediss://.\n\n  The same error also surfaces from kafka consumer workers when calling apply_async:\n\n  File \"celery/app/base.py\", line 970, in send_task\n      result = (result_cls or self.AsyncResult)(task_id)\n    File \"celery/backends/redis.py\", line 343, in _params_from_url\n      raise ValueError(E_REDIS_SSL_PARAMS_AND_SCHEME_MISMATCH)\n\n  Note: broker_use_ssl with redis:// works correctly in Kombu 5.6.2 (TLS connection is established). The inconsistency is exclusively in the backend validation.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-20T12:26:36Z",
